        {
          "ruleId": "bug/threading-safety",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "TOCTOU race in get_finding_store (check-then-act without lock)\n\nActual: get_finding_store() does \"if session_id not in self._stores\" followed by assignment without holding self._lock. Two concurrent callers can both pass the check and both create new FindingStore instances; one will overwrite the other, causing the loser to operate on a stale/orphaned store and lose findings.\nExpected: The check-and-create must be atomic. Wrap the entire method body in \"with self._lock\" or use a per-session lock to prevent double-initialization.\nSuggestion: [fix] Wrap lines 157-162 with \"with self._lock:\" to make the check-and-create atomic. Same pattern is needed for get_claim_registry, get_reaction_engine, get_message_bus, and get_event_bus which all share the identical bug.\nConfidence: 95% | Status: open"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/review_swarm/session_manager.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 156,
                  "endLine": 163
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "reviewswarm-id": "f-d38fc4",
            "expert_role": "threading-safety",
            "status": "open",
            "confidence": 0.95
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "bug/threading-safety",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "TOCTOU race in get_claim_registry, get_reaction_engine, get_message_bus, get_event_bus\n\nActual: All four lazy accessors (get_claim_registry lines 165-169, get_reaction_engine lines 171-180, get_message_bus lines 182-188, get_event_bus lines 190-196) use the same unprotected check-then-act pattern: read the dict, conditionally create, assign. None of them hold self._lock. Concurrent calls can create duplicate instances.\nExpected: Each lazy accessor should acquire self._lock before checking and creating the cached object, identical to the fix needed for get_finding_store.\nSuggestion: [fix] Wrap each method body with \"with self._lock:\". Alternatively, use a dict.setdefault pattern or functools.cached_property if possible, but the lock approach is simplest given the existing code structure.\nConfidence: 95% | Status: open"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/review_swarm/session_manager.py"
                },
                "region": {
